title: Test
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points.
Overall Unemployment rate has increased over the Year.

Unemployment rate is roughly constant from 1999 to 2001, gradually increasing from 2001 to 2003, roughly constant from 2003 to 2005, slightly decreasing from 2005 to 2006, roughly constant from 2006 to 2008, rapidly increasing from 2008 to 2009, roughly constant from 2009 to 2012, slightly increasing from 2012 to 2013, slightly decreasing from 2013 to 2014, and lastly roughly constant from 2014 to 2019.
The steepest increase occurs in between the Year 2008 and 2009.
Max Unemployment rate about 16.18 was recorded at Year 2013
Min Unemployment rate about 6.87 was recorded at Year 2001
This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Unemployment rate, with a total of 21 data points. The chart has 5 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely increasing which exists from 2006 to 2013.
Additionally, the next significant trend is extremely decreasing which exists from 1999 to 2003.
But, the next significant trend is moderately decreasing which exists from 2016 to 2019.
On the contrary, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2013 to 2016.
On the other hand, the next significant trend is slightly decreasing which exists from 2003 to 2006.
